Russell Wade Cooper (born 1955) is an American macroeconomist who is currently a professor at Pennsylvania State University in State College, PA. He has previously held academic positions at the University of Texas, Yale University, the University of Iowa, European University Institute and Boston University. He is best known for his work on coordination games. He is the author of the book Coordination Games, and the co-author of Dynamic Economics with Jerome Adda. An early work on multi-period insurance contracts with Beth Hayes is still regularly cited.
